{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"sole-teal-churn","description":"## Summary\n\nThe plan-review gate's Pass-2 **agentic verify** step (`verify_branch → verify`, prompt\n`plan-review-verifier-agentic`, `mode: structured`) truncates its output on finding-rich /\ncomplex plans: the model hits the per-call **output** token cap (`finish_reason=length`) before\nemitting the complete `plan_review_verification` structured result. The truncation aborts the\nverify step, so every finding it was verifying degrades to **indeterminate** and the whole review\nreturns **verdict = INDETERMINATE** (`verify_failed=true`) instead of a real PASS/BLOCK — even when\nthe find pass produced legitimate, actionable findings.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Take a finding-rich plan — reproduced live on epic `6c9c-811f-6dc4-40e7` (7 ACs, multi-file) and\n   task `2711-21bf-ab71-4136` (the reconciler cutover child). Both are in the store.\n2. Run `rebar review-plan <id> --output json`.\n3. Observe in the result:\n   - `coverage.verify_failed = true`\n   - `coverage.verify_error = \"step 'review@then/verify_branch@then/verify' failed: the model hit\n     the token cap before finishing (finish_reason=length) — its output is TRUNCATED; raise\n     max_tokens or split the step\"`\n   - `verdict = INDETERMINATE`, `counts.indeterminate` large (e.g. 30–35), `counts.blocking = 0`.\n\nFrequency: reproducible on complex plans (container epics, multi-file cutover tasks). Smaller plans\nverify fine, so it scales with finding count / verification output size.\n\n### Expected vs Actual\n\n- **Expected:** the verify step completes and returns a full `plan_review_verification`, yielding a\n  decisive PASS/BLOCK; a plan is only INDETERMINATE for genuine ambiguity, not because the verifier\n  ran out of output budget.\n- **Actual:** the verifier's structured output is cut off at the per-call `max_tokens`\n  (`finish_reason=length`), the step fails, and the review collapses to INDETERMINATE with all\n  candidate findings unverified.\n\n## Root-cause pointers\n\n- The error text is emitted by `src/rebar/llm/structured.py:193-194` (the `length` finish-reason\n  guard) via the stop-reason check at `src/rebar/llm/runner.py:456`.\n- The step is defined at `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/plan-review.yaml:130-146`. It already scales\n  its **turn/tool-call** budget with `step_budget_per_item: 25` (from bug 59bc), but that governs\n  agent turns, **not** the per-call output `max_tokens`.\n- The per-call output cap is `cfg.max_tokens` → `model_settings[\"max_tokens\"]`\n  (`src/rebar/llm/runner.py:252-259`), defaulting to `DEFAULT_MAX_TOKENS`\n  (`src/rebar/llm/config.py:266,471,535`). This is exactly the class of bug the find pass already\n  hit and fixed — see the comment at `runner.py:254-255`: the default \"4096 default — far too small\n  for a multi-child container review, whose output truncated (stop_reason=max_tokens)\". The verify\n  step needs the analogous treatment: scale its output cap with finding count, or split the step.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The agentic verify step no longer truncates on finding-rich plans: re-running\n      `rebar review-plan 6c9c-811f-6dc4-40e7` and `rebar review-plan 2711-21bf-ab71-4136` completes\n      the verify step (`verify_failed` absent/false) and returns a decisive PASS/BLOCK.\n- [ ] The verify step's per-call output `max_tokens` scales with the verification workload (e.g.\n      derived from finding count / `step_budget_per_item`, mirroring the find-pass fix at\n      `runner.py:252-259`) — or the step is split so each sub-call stays under the cap.\n- [ ] When the output cap is genuinely hit despite scaling, the failure is surfaced distinctly\n      (e.g. a dedicated \"verifier truncated\" signal) rather than silently degrading every finding to\n      indeterminate, so operators can tell a truncation from real ambiguity.\n- [ ] A regression test exercises a synthetic finding-rich verify input and asserts the step\n      completes (no `finish_reason=length`) with the scaled cap.\n- [ ] Non-integration suite green.","id":"4e6f-1a2d-482c-435e","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Plan-review agentic verify step truncates (finish_reason=length) on finding-rich plans -> whole review degrades to INDETERMINATE"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783221741355871001,"uuid":"ff9ee303-b6be-4031-803d-411e89f98224"}